article.headline: Sacred Heart 67, Army 52
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Kibwe Trim scored 13 of his team-high 16 points in the second half to lead Sacred Heart to a 67-52 win over Army Monday. Joey Henley had 14 points and Drew Shubik added 11 points for the Pioneers (1-1). Trim finished with eight rebounds as the Pioneers built a 31-23 edge on the glass. Sacred Heart led 29-21 at halftime despite shooting 39.3 percent from the field. But the Pioneers outscored Army 15-7 over the first five minutes of the second half to build a 44-28 cushion. The Black Knights (0-2) rallied to within seven points, 46-39, with 11:13 to play. But they'd get no closer the rest of the way. Army's Matt Bell scored a career-high 26 points, making 5 of 6 3-pointers. Colin Harris added 11 points for the Black Knights.
